tool_input.script:
export const meta = {
  name: 'qa-csp',
  description: 'QA: CSP設定 in Nablarch web app',
  phases: [
    { title: 'SemanticSearch', detail: 'search relevant knowledge pages' },
    { title: 'ReadSections', detail: 'read selected sections' },
    { title: 'GenerateAnswer', detail: 'generate Japanese answer' }
  ]
}

phase('SemanticSearch')
const searchResult = await agent(
  `Execute the semantic search workflow at workflows/semantic-search.md in the directory /home/tie303177/work/nabledge/work2/.claude/skills/nabledge-6.

Query: "Content Security Policyを有効にしたい。NablarchのWeb画面でCSPを設定するにはどうすればいい？（処理方式: ウェブアプリケーション）（目的: セキュリティ対応したい）"

The knowledge files are located at: /home/tie303177/work/nabledge/work2/.claude/skills/nabledge-6/knowledge/

Read workflows/semantic-search.md first and follow it exactly.

Return a JSON object with:
{
  "selected_sections": [
    {"file": "<full path to json file>", "section_id": "<sN>", "relevance": "<high|partial>", "reason": "<why selected>"}
  ],
  "selected_pages": [
    {"path": "<page path relative to knowledge/>", "reason": "<why selected>"}
  ],
  "excluded_pages": [
    {"path": "<page path relative to knowledge/>", "reason": "<why excluded>"}
  ],
  "excluded_sections": [
    {"file": "<full path>", "section_id": "<sN>", "reason": "<why excluded>"}
  ]
}`,
  {
    label: 'semantic-search',
    phase: 'SemanticSearch',
    schema: {
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        selected_sections: {
          type: 'array',
          items: {
            type: 'object',
            properties: {
              file: { type: 'string' },
              section_id: { type: 'string' },
              relevance: { type: 'string', enum: ['high', 'partial'] },
              reason: { type: 'string' }
            },
            required: ['file', 'section_id', 'relevance', 'reason']
          }
        },
        selected_pages: {
          type: 'array',
          items: {
            type: 'object',
            properties: {
              path: { type: 'string' },
              reason: { type: 'string' }
            },
            required: ['path', 'reason']
          }
        },
        excluded_pages: {
          type: 'array',
          items: {
            type: 'object',
            properties: {
              path: { type: 'string' },
              reason: { type: 'string' }
            },
            required: ['path', 'reason']
          }
        },
        excluded_sections: {
          type: 'array',
          items: {
            type: 'object',
            properties: {
              file: { type: 'string' },
              section_id: { type: 'string' },
              reason: { type: 'string' }
            },
            required: ['file', 'section_id', 'reason']
          }
        }
      },
      required: ['selected_sections', 'selected_pages', 'excluded_pages', 'excluded_sections']
    }
  }
)

log(`Selected ${searchResult.selected_sections.length} sections`)

phase('ReadSections')
// Select up to 10 sections: high first, then partial
const highSections = searchResult.selected_sections.filter(s => s.relevance === 'high')
const partialSections = searchResult.selected_sections.filter(s => s.relevance === 'partial')
const sectionsToRead = [...highSections, ...partialSections].slice(0, 10)

const readArgs = sectionsToRead.map(s => `"${s.file}:${s.section_id}"`).join(' ')
log(`Reading sections: ${readArgs}`)

const sectionsContent = await agent(
  `Run this exact bash command and return its complete stdout output:

bash /home/tie303177/work/nabledge/work2/.claude/skills/nabledge-6/scripts/read-sections.sh ${readArgs}

Return the raw text output from the command.`,
  { label: 'read-sections', phase: 'ReadSections' }
)

phase('GenerateAnswer')
const answerResult = await agent(
  `You are a Nablarch expert. Generate a Japanese answer to the following question based on the provided knowledge sections.

## Question
Content Security Policyを有効にしたい。NablarchのWeb画面でCSPを設定するにはどうすればいい？（処理方式: ウェブアプリケーション）（目的: セキュリティ対応したい）

## Knowledge sections content
${sectionsContent}

## Sections that were read (for reference tracking)
${sectionsToRead.map(s => s.file + ':' + s.section_id).join(', ')}

## Instructions

Generate a Japanese answer in this format:

**結論**: Direct answer to the question (1–2 sentences)
- Include specific method names, class names, and approaches

**根拠**: Code examples, configuration examples, or spec information
- Show code/config examples in code blocks
- Quote code examples from sections verbatim

**注意点**: Constraints, common mistakes (omit if nothing applies)

参照: Only sections actually cited (file.json:sN format, omit category path)

Stay within 500 tokens (up to 800 for complex questions).

Then verify: Check all Nablarch-specific claims (API names, class names, config methods, behavior specs, constraints, parameters) are supported by the sections content. 

If any claim is unsupported, regenerate the answer without those claims.

Return a JSON object:
{
  "final_answer": "<the verified Japanese answer text>",
  "verify_result": "PASS" or "FAIL",
  "verify_issues": ["<unsupported claim if any>"],
  "answer_sections_used": [{"ref": "<file.json:sN>", "reason": "<why used>"}],
  "answer_sections_unused": [{"ref": "<file.json:sN>", "reason": "<why not used>"}]
}`,
  {
    label: 'generate-answer',
    phase: 'GenerateAnswer',
    schema: {
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        final_answer: { type: 'string' },
        verify_result: { type: 'string', enum: ['PASS', 'FAIL'] },
        verify_issues: { type: 'array', items: { type: 'string' } },
        answer_sections_used: {
          type: 'array',
          items: {
            type: 'object',
            properties: {
              ref: { type: 'string' },
              reason: { type: 'string' }
            },
            required: ['ref', 'reason']
          }
        },
        answer_sections_unused: {
          type: 'array',
          items: {
            type: 'object',
            properties: {
              ref: { type: 'string' },
              reason: { type: 'string' }
            },
            required: ['ref', 'reason']
          }
        }
      },
      required: ['final_answer', 'verify_result', 'answer_sections_used', 'answer_sections_unused']
    }
  }
)

return {
  searchResult,
  sectionsToRead,
  answerResult
}
